<subSubSection pageId="136" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="136.[151,1437,1302,1510]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
This worldwide, but predominantly tropical, family of acalyptrate flies contains 640 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[1191,1359,1339,1365]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." pageId="136" pageNumber="137" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[384,571,1375,1401]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[584,642,1374,1401]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="357 - 372" refId="ref368282" refString="Rondani, C. (1851) Dipterorum species aliquae in America aequatoriali collectae a Cajetano Osculati observatae et distinctae novis breviter descriptis. Nuovi Annali delle Scienze Naturali e Rendiconto delle Sessioni della Societa Agraria e dell'Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna, Series 3, 2 [1850], 357 - 372." type="journal article" year="1851">1851</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[657,716,1375,1401]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" refId="ref369190" refString="Rondani, C. (1863) Diptera exotica revisa et annotata novis nonnullis descriptis. Eredi Soliani, Modena, 99 pp., 1 pl. [This is the separate that came out before the journal version with a different title, here as Rondani (1864 a)]." type="book" year="1863">1863</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[729,799,1374,1401]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="421 - 464" refId="ref371012" refString="Rondani, C. (1875 c) Muscaria exotica Musei Civici Januensis observata et distincta. Fragmentum III. Species in Insula Bonae Fortunae (Borneo), Provincia Sarawak, annis 1865 - 68, lectae a March. J. Doria et Doct. O. Beccari. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 421 - 464." type="journal article" year="1875">1875c</bibRefCitation>
) described five Neotropical and three 
<collectingRegion box="[1243,1335,1375,1401]" country="Morocco" name="Oriental" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Oriental</collectingRegion>
nominal species. Six are currently considered as valid, two as junior synonyms (
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[965,1141,1411,1437]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref375199" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1968 a) Family Micropezidae. In: Papavero, N. (Ed.), A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria de Agricultura, Sao Paulo, 48, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1968">Steyskal 1968a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[1154,1225,1411,1437]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="12 - 20" refId="ref375364" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1977 a) Family Micropezidae. In: Delfinado, M. D. &amp; Hardy, D. E. (Eds.), A catalog of the Diptera of the Oriental Region. Volume III. Suborder Cyclorrhapha (excluding Division Aschiza). University of Hawaii Press, Honolulu, pp. 12 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1977">1977a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferro, G. B. &amp; Marshall, S. A." pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="401 - 458" refId="ref350583" refString="Ferro, G. B. &amp; Marshall, S. A. (2018) A revision of the Neotropical ant-like genus Cardiacephala Macquart, including Plocoscelus Enderlein, syn. nov. (Diptera: Micropezidae: Taeniapterinae). Zootaxa, 4429 (3), 401 - 458. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4429.3.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ferro &amp; Marshall 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Except for the 
<typeStatus box="[397,445,1447,1473]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
material of two species, which are presumed lost, the remaining 
<typeStatus box="[1175,1223,1447,1473]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
material is distributed between the MZUN (three) and MSNG (three).
</paragraph>
